com.foreach.across.modules.entity.registry.properties

Interface ConfigurableEntityPropertyController<T,U>

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    GenericEntityPropertyController, NestedEntityPropertyController

    public interface ConfigurableEntityPropertyController<T,U>
    Builder-like interface for customizing a GenericEntityPropertyController. Allows strong-typing and scoping a controller using one of the withTarget(Class, Class), withEntity(Class, Class) or withBindingContext(Class) methods. This makes it easier to apply configuration with strong-typed parameters.
    Since:
    3.2.0
    Author:
    Arne Vandamme
    See Also:
    EntityPropertyController, ScopedConfigurableEntityPropertyController

      • bulkValueFetcher

        ConfigurableEntityPropertyController<T,U> bulkValueFetcher(Function<Collection<T>,Map<T,U>> valueFetcher)
        Set the value fetching function that should be used for retrieving this property value in bulk from a collection of entities. Setting a non-null bulk fetcher should automatically also set optimizedForBulkValueFetching(boolean) to true.

        Custom implementations should preferably return an IdentityHashMap to ensure that all input items have a corresponding value entry. Even if they are equals, separate entries are still expected. The order of the items returned is not important.

        Parameters:
        valueFetcher - to use
        Returns:
        self

      • optimizedForBulkValueFetching

        ConfigurableEntityPropertyController<T,U> optimizedForBulkValueFetching(boolean optimized)
        Explicitly flag that this controller is optimized for bulk value fetching. This is usually done automatically if a non-null bulkValueFetcher(Function) was configured.
        Parameters:
        optimized - true if EntityPropertyController.isOptimizedForBulkValueFetching() should return true
        Returns:
        self

      • applyValueConsumer

        ConfigurableEntityPropertyController<T,U> applyValueConsumer(BiConsumer<T,EntityPropertyValue<U>> valueWriter)
        Set the consumer that should be called when applying the property value using EntityPropertyController.applyValue(EntityPropertyBindingContext, EntityPropertyValue). The return value of calling EntityPropertyController.applyValue(EntityPropertyBindingContext, EntityPropertyValue) will always be true if you specify a BiConsumer. See applyValueFunction(BiFunction) if you want to control the return value.
        Parameters:
        valueWriter - consumer for setting the value
        Returns:
        self
